This paper discusses a caching algorithm for computer networks, which falls under the category of network optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses distributed and online algorithms, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The algorithm is based on content popularity, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses incentives for nodes and quality of service guarantees for content owners, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
